            },
            {
               "text": "<p><table class=\"book_navigation\"><tr><td>Soroban (算盤)</td><td>Suanpan (算盤)</td></tr><tr><td><img id=\"imgSoroban\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgSoroban', '0%')\" src=\"\" class=\"imgcenter\" style=\"width: 100%\"/></td><td><img id=\"imgSuanpan\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgSuanpan', '0%')\" src=\"\" style=\"width: 73%\"/></td></tr></table></p><p class=\"desc\"><b>Figura 1</b>: Ábacos. À esquerda, temos um Soroban (算盤) de Shigetoshi Oyabu. Mantido por Tohoku University Main Library (<htcite0>). À direita, temos um Suanpan (算盤). © Trustees of the British Museum (<htcite1>)</p>",
